### PostGRESql/PostGIS Database

`GoogleEncodedPolyline.sql` contains three functions necessary to support this implementation of Google's polyline encoding algorithm. Add these functions to your PostGIS-enabled PostGRESql database in order to perform the encodings directly in the data layer, rather than in some middleware technology (e.g. PHP, etc).

Note that this implementation will encode either multipart POLYLINE or multipart POLYGON features, including polygon features with interior rings (a.k.a. holes).

To `SELECT` a feature geometry's encoding using this implementation, you'd query it like this:

```
SELECT GoogleEncodePolygon(the_geom) from StateParks where name = 'Sequicentennial State Park';
```
